Reasoning: The paper deals with network coding, specifically fractional linear network codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the properties of networks and their solvability, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it deals with the transmission of messages through a network. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of distributed systems (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC) as it discusses the solvability of networks with different dimensions and complexities.
